						<summary>

						<p>Slab kept in the Jaina temple.</p>						

						<p>Vikramāditya-VI A.D. 1121.</p>						

						<p>This damaged inscription referring itself to the reign of Tribhuvanamalladēva is dated in the Chālukya-Vikrama year 46, Plava, Pushya śu. 13. These details correspond to A.D. 1121, December 23, Friday.</p>						

						<p>It registers a gift made to the sage Vāsupūjya for the benefit of the Jaina temple constructed by Jayakarṇa the beloved son of Vikramāchāri. The record is published in <hi rend="italic">JBBRAS,</hi> Vol. X, pp. 287 ff.</p>						

						</summary>
